Most of the content is already on his YouTube channel but I thought in this case it was worth paying for the additional content. You get his monologue, which is pretty funny and sets up some of the following jokes. The audio on Spark of Insanity was a little hard to follow at times, but I can chalk that up to my sound system. If you have seen his YouTube videos you might find his humor a little highschoolish and repetitious, but acceptable considering what passes for comedy lately. Topics might be a little passe and what was funny in 2009 might not get past the SJW's today. All in all it was worth it to me.

Great value for the money! Its a great deal to be able to get 2 individual DVDs packaged as a set. I was expecting one DVD with two features and I was pleasantly surprised to see that they were actually 2 complete DVDs packaged together. He does not disappoint in his performances. Not all his current characters are in these DVDs since these are 2 of his earliest DVDs but if you're a fan of his, you won't be disappointed because he is very talented. His material is very funny, original and entertaining.

Jeff Dunham is one most talented ventriloquists ever.  This Double feature has 2 of Jeff's best shows

During the show it appears that the puppets are in control.  He not only brings them to life, he plays a role himself.  I never tire of Peanut, Achmed, Jose, or  Walter .  Each is so alive and hilarious.  Often Jeff has 2 or more puppets interacting with each other.

.

As usual, Jeff Dunham has created some outlandish and good fun with his puppets - I really enjoy these live performances captured on DVD and can enjoy them with all family members! This is a real buy, since there are two separate programs in the same package. Lots of laughs and we can watch them later and they are still hilarious. Great entertainment for a very reasonable price.
